items.title: South Korea's President Yoon declares martial law
items.author: Reuters
items.content:
President Yoon Suk Yeol declared martial law on Dec. 3 and triggered a short-lived attempt by troops to enter parliament, as lawmakers and protesters quickly voiced opposition to the most serious challenge to the country's democracy since the 1980s.
